elings. Right now he is happy because he likes to read with us."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Equity Sticks during reading to choose children to share their responses."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read aloud the book and the Day 2 prompts."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 3 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Look at the boy playing the guitar and singing. Let’s pretend to play guitar and sing. How do you feel? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"feelings"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 5"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"These children have faces of all different colors. How can you tell they are all happy? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 18"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This boy has tears falling from his eyes. Who is he sharing his sad feelings with? Who do you like to share your feelings with? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"share"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 19"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Which dog is sad? Which dog is proud? Sometimes you can tell how someone feels by the look on her face. Can you show me a happy face? A mad face? A sad face? A proud face? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 25"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The little mouse does not want the cat to come in, so he says “NO!” in a big voice. We can use our words to tell others how we feel. Say, “NO!” in a big voice. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to stand in a circle and play a happy game. Tell children to follow along and join in doing things that make us happy.   Say, “Jumping makes me happy, so let’s jump, jump, jump.” Then say: “Hopping makes me happy, so let’s hop, hop, hop.” Continue with dancing, clapping, and twisting. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcribe children’s speech as they talk about how they feel when they do a favorite activity."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Mind Builder"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Remember that children may not have the words to say what they’re feeling. Point out an emotion a child is showing, such as feeling proud, and ask questions about how and why they’re feeling that way. Giving them words to describe the feeling can help them with relationships and their own mental and emotional health."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_3","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"ME AND YOU"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 1: All About Me"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Build Background"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk about being like someone else. Give examples such as,“I like  purple; clap if you’re like me,” “I like fruit; clap if you’re like me,” and “I like to draw; clap if you’re like me.”"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"“The Alphabet Song”"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to join in as you sing “The Alphabet Song.” Then take a walk around the room and have children point out where they see letters. Read any words to them.  "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce a new word that will help children talk about their feelings. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 1.1.3 Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"brave"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to reread the book "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Be Who You Are"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Todd Parr."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Pablo Stick Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The book we will read is about things that make us who we are.Pablo loves to learn about children and the things they do that make them who they are."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements"